#Adipurush might well be the biggest Bollywood debacle of all times. It has faced severe public criticism, protests from Hindu organisations, disapproval of own cast, condemnation from the team behind the superhit Ramayan serial, threats of theatre boycotts, petitions to halt its screening and scathing comments from Allahabad high court

So what really went so wrong? A variety of reasons ranging from the makers dismissing audience feedback, disregarding Hindu sentiments, displaying arrogance when humility was needed, leaving a minor player to do all the fire-fighting, assuming political endorsement will shape public opinion and so on

For years, the industry has interacted with a select group from the public and, that too, only from their balconies where they wave their hands or throw a flying kiss. This arrogance, despite a track record of poor quality plagiarised products, worked till new realisations dawned on the public in recent years. Now the tide has changed.
